						               													<description>Players are elfs who are seeking for gold while crossing a giant Rainbow. Running fast may guarantee them to be the first to arrive on the Pot of Gold at the other side. The player who collects more gold coins or the one who arrives first at the Pot wins. It's a game of pushing your luck and trying to trick your opponents. In each move players will try to guess if the next card is higher or lower than the previous one, to advance one step. Some lightenings are played against the others to try to fool them and make them return to the beginning while clowds are used as a protection. A player collects as many gold coins as the cards of the same color correctly revealed, when he decides to stop. Some simple tactics and a lot of interaction awaits you in this Pot-o-Gold Run!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In October 2012 the game was finalist in the Boardgame Design Contest of Panzazol Joue (France).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
